    "sourceEnglish": "In Aesop's Fables, one reads: \"An ass put on the skin of a lion and went around frightening all the animals. The ass saw a fox and tried to frighten her too, but she had heard his voice first, so she said to the ass, 'You can be sure that I too would have been afraid, if I had not already heard the sound of your bray'.\" The moral is:"
